So Jasper stops feeling sorry for herself and accepts that she can't be perfect. She abandons her sword and shield and takes up the path of the monk, hoping that perhaps she can continue to enlighten herself as time goes on.

Then towards the end of Stormblood, Jasper fights Omega and realizes that strength isn't what matters but one's own conviction and heart. Punishing herself won't make her stronger, only moving past her mistakes will.

So Jasper was like super depressed through the entirety of Stormblood because her constant failures led her to believe that she needed to punish herself in order to get better. So throughout Stormblood she was basically beating herself up which only made things worse.
